            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="The Eiffel Tower, or La Tour Eiffel, is an iconic iron lattice structure located on the Champ de Mars in Paris, France. Completed in 1889 for the Exposition Universelle (Worldâ€™s Fair) to celebrate the 100th anniversary of the French Revolution, it was designed by the engineer Gustave Eiffel and initially met with criticism from artists and intellectuals. Today, it stands as a global symbol of innovation, romance, and the enduring spirit of France.
\n\nRising 330 meters (1,083 feet) high, the tower was the worldâ€™s tallest man-made structure until the completion of the Chrysler Building in New York in 1930. It consists of over 18,000 iron pieces held together by 2.5 million rivets, showcasing remarkable 19th-century engineering precision. The structure weighs around 10,100 tons yet appears light and airy due to its lattice design.
\n\nThe tower has three public levels â€” restaurants and shops on the first two floors, and a breathtaking observation deck on the third, offering panoramic views of Paris and landmarks like the Seine River, Notre-Dame, and the Louvre. Illuminated by more than 20,000 sparkling lights each evening, it transforms the Parisian skyline into a vision of beauty and wonder.
\n\nOriginally intended to be dismantled after 20 years, the Eiffel Tower survived due to its usefulness as a radio transmission tower. Today, it welcomes over 7 million visitors annually and continues to embody the elegance, artistry, and technological brilliance that define French culture."
                android:textColor="#CFCFCF"
                android:textSize="15sp"
                android:lineSpacingExtra="4dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="20dp" />

